Minister of Investment and International Cooperation Sahar Nasr on Wednesday 17/1/2018 reached an agreement with her Ethiopian counterpart Fitsum Arega to set up a joint investment council. The council will group businessmen and investors from both sides, according to a statement issued by the Investment Ministry. At a meeting in Egypt, Nasr expounded investment opportunities in Egypt in several domains, added the statement. She urged her Ethiopian counterpart to encourage investors from his country to invest in Egypt.